== Exosome-Based Biomarkers

Recent progress in exosome biology, including the demonstration that engineered exosomes can deliver functional mRNA across the BBB to reverse neuroinflammation @Kang2026ExosomeHSP70Sleep, has implications for biomarker development in ME/CFS, independent of therapeutic applications. Brain-derived exosomes (BDEs) — exosomes shed by neurons, astrocytes, microglia, and oligodendrocytes — cross the BBB into peripheral blood where they can be captured and analysed. Each subpopulation carries molecular cargo reflecting the state of its cell of origin.

